# .cursorrules — FaithfulChain

# Identity
You are building FaithfulChain, a reasoning faithfulness auditor for AI chain-of-thought.
This is a research project for the Anthropic Fellows Program.
Read CLAUDE.md before writing any code.

# File structure authority
architecture.md is the source of truth for file locations.
Do not create files outside the structure defined there without documenting the addition.

# Code quality rules
- Python: always use type hints, async def for all I/O, docstrings on every function
- React: functional components only, Tailwind CSS only, no inline styles
- Never hardcode secrets. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY comes from .env only.
- Wrap all json.loads() in try/except in Python.
- All Claude API calls go through backend/claude_service.py only.
- All Axios calls go through frontend/src/api.js only.

# Testing rules
- Every logic function needs a test before it is considered done.
- Mock the Claude API in all tests — tests must pass without a real API key.
- Run pytest before saying backend work is complete.

# Prompts
The two Claude system prompts (REASONER_SYSTEM, AUDITOR_SYSTEM) are defined in CLAUDE.md.
Copy them exactly into backend/prompts.py. Do not paraphrase or shorten them.

# What not to do
- Do not use LangChain
- Do not use Redux
- Do not use a database (JSONL flat file only)
- Do not write custom CSS (Tailwind only)
- Do not commit .env

# Progress tracking
After completing work, update progress.md and check off items in implementation-plan.md.
